# Connections (multi-provider)

Every health-data integration follows the same seams. Full guide with steps:
`docs/integrations.md`. Garmin (`features/garmin-connect/`) is the reference
implementation.

## Key pieces

- `connections/lib/provider.ts` — `HealthDataProvider` contract every provider
  implements: `getConnection`, `disconnect`, `getDevice?`, `fetchDailyMetrics`.
- `connections/lib/registry.ts` — domain registry (`id → implementation`) and
  `PROVIDER_PRIORITY` (field-by-field merge order). Register new adapters here.
- `connections/providers.ts` — UI registry (name, tagline, `Icon`, static
  `accentClass`, capabilities). Future providers are NOT announced by brand;
  the hub shows one generic `ComingSoonCard`.
- `connections/lib/connections-service.ts` — generic status/device/disconnect,
  served by `/api/connections/[provider]/*` routes.
- `connections/lib/linked-account-repository.ts` — `linked_accounts` table
  (one row per user+provider). Never store tokens in D1.
- `shared/lib/token-vault.ts` — encrypted secrets in KV under
  `<provider>_tokens:<userId>`. Also intended for future BYOK AI keys.
- `sync/lib/sync-service.ts` — provider-agnostic; persists metrics with
  `source = provider.id` into `daily_metrics (user_id, date, source)`.

## Adding a provider (summary)

1. Extend `ProviderId` + add entry in `connections/providers.ts`.
2. Implement link flow in `features/<provider>-connect/lib/` (tokens via
   `saveProviderTokens`, account via `LinkedAccountRepository.upsert`).
3. Write `<provider>-metrics-source.ts` returning `DailyMetric` (nullable
   fields; never fail a whole day for one metric).
4. Create `<provider>-provider.ts` implementing `HealthDataProvider`.
5. Register it in `registry.ts` (`HEALTH_PROVIDERS` + `PROVIDER_PRIORITY`).
6. Add `<Provider>ConnectionCard.tsx` + register in `AVAILABLE_CARDS`
   (`ConnectionsApp.tsx`).

## Conventions

- `accentClass` must be a static Tailwind literal (scanner requirement).
- Cards stay presentational; network/state-machine logic lives in hooks.
- Invalidate `['garmin-status']`-style query keys plus `['metrics']` after
  connect/disconnect/sync so dashboards refresh.
- Metrics reads: `source` param = single integration; no `source` = merged
  view (`mergeRowsByDate` in `metrics-service.ts`) — the future AI layer will
  consume this merged read.
